Nashville Hot Chicken

- 5 (or so) chicken thighs
- kosher salt
Generously salt chicken thighs and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

- 1 cup buttermilk
- 1/4 cup pickle juice
- 2 Tbsp Sriracha or other hot sauce
- 1 egg
Make marinade by whisking together buttermilk, pickle juice, hot sauce and egg, and put in a gallon ziptop bag.
Put chicken thighs into marinade for at least 2 hours.

- 2 cups flour
- 2 tsp table salt
Mix flour and table salt in a wide dish or bowl.
One at a time, shake off marinade from thighs, then coat with flour, then dunk back in marinade, then coat with flour again.
Let rest on a rack for about 15 minutes before cooking.

- 1/4 cup butter
- 1/4 cup lard
- 1/2 Tbsp cayenne pepper (or up to 2 Tbsp for extra spicy)
- 1 Tbsp brown sugar
- 1 tsp paprika
- 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1/2 tsp kosher salt
- 1/2 tsp black pepper
Melt butter and lard over very low heat. Mix in cayenne, brown sugar, paprika, garlic powder, kosher salt and black pepper.

- vegetable oil
Preheat oven to 200F if frying in batches
In a small pot, pour about 1 inch of oil, and heat to about 350-375F.
Place chicken into oil and adjust heat to maintain a temperature of about 325F.
Cook until internal temperature is at least 160F.
Store cooked thighs in heated oven while frying subsequent batches.

Brush chicken with lard/spice mixture.
Serve on white bread with lots of pickles.
